    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "After consulting with @richard-ramos there are 2 possible improvements\r\n- use context timeout in status-go/stickers - this way, the long operation will automatically close goroutines with requests, if they last too long\r\n- additionally use nim thread pool and run function asynchronously\r\n\r\nThere is no good way to check connection by Qt. This requires pinging a server that we trust. \r\nSee https://forum.qt.io/topic/98676/how-to-check-whether-the-computer-connects-the-internet/8\r\nAlso there are a few native ways, which means we should handle 3 different implementations. \r\nHowever, regarding stickers, first we should apply context timeouts.",
